Minimal personal dotfiles.

Files of interest:
- `profile/bash_profile`
- `profile/bashrc`
- `profile/zshrc`
- `profile/gitconfig`
- `profile/tmux.conf`
- `config/nvim/init.lua`

Setup

1. Clone the repo to either `~/dotfiles` or `~/.dotfiles`
2. Symlink the files you want into `$HOME`
3. Put machine- or work-specific environment variables in either:
   - `inc/envs.local`
   - `~/.config/shell/envs.local`

Example:

```bash
git clone git@github.com:metaphox/dotfiles.git ~/dotfiles
ln -s ~/dotfiles/profile/bashrc ~/.bashrc
ln -s ~/dotfiles/profile/bash_profile ~/.bash_profile
ln -s ~/dotfiles/profile/zshrc ~/.zshrc
ln -s ~/dotfiles/profile/gitconfig ~/.gitconfig
ln -s ~/dotfiles/profile/tmux.conf ~/.tmux.conf
```

Single-file examples:

```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/metaphox/dotfiles/master/profile/tmux.conf -o ~/.tmux.conf
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/metaphox/dotfiles/master/vimrc_minimum -o ~/.vimrc
```
